OL,3,CParents hid trackers in toys to see
OL,4,Cwhere kids 'could be snatched', judge
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FHe added that the parents were
OL,8,Fcontacted, and denied knowing anything
OL,9,Fabout the devices, and made counter-
OL,10,Faccusations against the local
OL,11,Fauthority concerned in proceedings
OL,12,Fabout whether they had done this
OL,13,Fdeliberately to discredit them.
OL,15,FIn later statements to the court in
OL,16,FLiverpool, the mother accepted sole
OL,17,Fresponsibility for the idea of
OL,18,Fpurchasing trackers and for the
OL,19,Fexecution of the plan, but the judge
OL,20,Fdid not accept that the father would
OL,21,Fnot have known.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
