OL,3,CParents hid trackers in toys to see
OL,4,Cwhere kids 'could be snatched', judge
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FIn his written judgment, he continued:
OL,8,F"I do not believe what the parents
OL,9,Ftell me and I reject their evidence,
OL,10,Fnot just when it conflicts with other
OL,11,Fevidence before me, but when it does
OL,12,Fnot, too.
OL,14,F"In my judgment, the decision to use
OL,15,Ftracking devices was a parental
OL,16,Fdecision and one in which the father
OL,17,Fwas a full participant.
OL,26,@pD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
