OL,3,CParents hid trackers in toys to see
OL,4,Cwhere kids 'could be snatched', judge
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FHe also said: "These devices were part
OL,8,Fof a wider plan to know where the
OL,9,Fchildren were, either in terms of
OL,10,Fwhere they were living, or from where
OL,11,Fthey could be snatched. And probably
OL,12,Fboth."
OL,14,FJudge Sharpe also found that the
OL,15,Fparents had made a "concerted effort
OL,16,Fto conceal the truth" by not handing
OL,17,Fover their phones so that they could
OL,18,Fbe examined in relation to the
OL,19,Ftracking devices.
